# Docker image build

When the user asks to **build the image** (or "build Docker", "rebuild image", etc.):

- **Production:** `npm run build-docker:prod` — builds production stage image and starts container (uses `.env.production`).
- **Local / dev:** `npm run build-docker:dev` — builds development stage image and starts container (uses `.env` only, not `.env.production`).

Both use Docker Compose under the hood; image name is **pure**.

## Allowed alternatives

- `docker compose build` is acceptable for build-only workflows (for example, CI/local troubleshooting when you do not want to start containers).
- Prefer `npm run build-docker:*` for normal project workflows because it uses repo defaults consistently.
- Do **not** use raw `docker build --target ...` for this project.

## Post-build checks

- Confirm build completes without Dockerfile or compose errors.
- Confirm expected environment source was used (`.env` for dev, `.env.production` for prod).
- If container startup is part of the request, verify services are running after the command.
